<p class="p">We further deconstruct the total amount distribution simulated by CAM into contributions from parameterized convective and resolved large‐scale processes in order to unfold their influence on rain rates across the distribution. The amount distributions for total (
 <italic class="italic">p
  <sup class="sup">T</sup>
 </italic>), convective (
 <italic class="italic">p
  <sup class="sup">C</sup>
 </italic>), and large‐scale (
 <italic class="italic">p
  <sup class="sup">L</sup>
 </italic>) precipitation contributions, respectively, are given by: 
 <disp-formula id="jame20562-disp-0002" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">(2)</label>
  <math id="nlm-math-11" class="math">
   <msubsup class="msubsup">
